<Author>JohnnyUtah75
<Content>Absolutely loved this Hotel! My wife and I traveled to Spain for our Honeymoon and stayed at this hotel for our first 2 nights before traveling on. We loved this hotel... conveniently located right in front of the Train station made getting to and from the airport a breeze! Also, located in the charming area of El Born which had great food, bars and walking distance to everything.... minus the Gaudi Church and Parc Guell. Close to the beach, Las Ramblas, Barri Gotic, picasso museum, Santa Maria del Mar, Catedral and more.. Read some reviews about the bad breakfast but we found it to be amazing... Huge with plenty of options to choose from. Tasty meats and cheeses, fresh juice and fruit, eggs, bacon, cereal, yogurt, breads, etc... Upon the end of our 2 week trip we flew out of Barcelona and decided to stay in the L'Eixample area on the last night... big mistake. Our hotel there was great but the area is nothing compared to what surrounds this gem! We loved the Park Hotel and if we ever return to Barcelona we will definitely stay here! Do bring earplugs if you're a light sleeper and you're staying on the weekend. 
