<Content>Good Value and Great Location I decided to stay here after reading a glowing review in an article in the Conde Nast Traveller magazine (April 2006 issue) featuring stylish and affordable hotels in Barcelona. The facade first catches the eye with its distinctive architectural style. The rooms are mimimalist in style and are very clean. The mattress was very firm which I like however the pillows were these tube-shaped ones which I don't particularly care for.The breakfast buffet was wonderful and I understand that the restaurant is considered one of the best in the city. Not much in terms of amenities but at 120 Euro for a Double you can't expect too much. There is a Plasma DVD however the only English-language station I could find was BBC World.The only complaint was that it was unseasonably warm however it was not possible to cool the room as the ventilation system had not yet been switched over to the a/c.The hotel is situated in the El Born district not far from the Barceloneta beach. A lot of traffic passes in front of the hotel so make sure to ask for a room that's not facing the main street. 
